(Lee Si Woo)

4
00:00:17,230 --> 00:00:19,630
(Yoon Se A)

5
00:00:26,700 --> 00:00:28,840
(Chang Ryul)

6
00:00:34,840 --> 00:00:36,850
(Dahyun)

7
00:00:41,980 --> 00:00:46,520
(Love Me)

8
00:00:56,890 --> 00:01:02,200
(Love me)

9
00:01:02,260 --> 00:01:07,770
(Love me)

10
00:01:20,720 --> 00:01:21,720
By the way,

11
00:01:22,920 --> 00:01:24,350
how come your boyfriend didn't make it today?

12
00:01:24,820 --> 00:01:25,890
Sorry?

13
00:01:26,660 --> 00:01:28,360
I was hoping to finally meet him.

14
00:01:31,360 --> 00:01:32,760
What did you say he does for a living?

15
00:01:33,460 --> 00:01:35,130
She said he'll be a professor soon.

16
00:01:36,030 --> 00:01:38,599
No, he's a lecturer, not a professor.

17
00:01:38,600 --> 00:01:39,600
I see.

18
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:43,310
He'll get there eventually. Goodness.

19
00:01:44,040 --> 00:01:46,940
A star writer and a professor. What a power couple.

20
00:01:48,110 --> 00:01:49,810
See? Now I'm even more curious.

21
00:01:50,580 --> 00:01:51,680
You should've told him to come.

22
00:01:51,980 --> 00:01:53,780
I guess he's a little busy.

23
00:01:54,250 --> 00:01:58,450
What? Come on. His girlfriend won a major award,

24
00:01:58,750 --> 00:01:59,960
and he's "too busy"?

25
00:02:03,090 --> 00:02:04,130
Come on, let's go.

26
00:02:05,060 --> 00:02:06,430
All right, thanks.

27
00:02:07,830 --> 00:02:10,000
You guys go on ahead. I'll be right in.

28
00:02:10,130 --> 00:02:12,270
Why? Are you going to call your boyfriend?

29
00:02:12,430 --> 00:02:14,470
Tell him to come, even if it's late. I really want to meet him.

30
00:02:17,010 --> 00:02:18,010
Hey.

31
00:02:18,910 --> 00:02:19,910
Hey!

32
00:02:28,380 --> 00:02:29,890
Is this why you didn't show up?

33
00:02:30,620 --> 00:02:33,120
- You can see for yourself.
- Why are you working as a driver?

34
00:02:33,190 --> 00:02:34,660
I need the money. Am I doing this for fun?

35
00:02:34,720 --> 00:02:37,830
That's what I'm asking! What could you need the money for?

36
00:02:39,230 --> 00:02:41,299
- I'm busy. I got a ride request.
- Seo Jun Seo.

37
00:02:41,300 --> 00:02:42,530
For a nobody to become a lecturer,

38
00:02:44,430 --> 00:02:45,970
they said I have to pay 5,000 dollars.

39
00:02:47,370 --> 00:02:49,000
They said it's the only way. What else can I do?

40
00:02:51,140 --> 00:02:52,640
You can't be serious.

41
00:02:54,380 --> 00:02:56,080
You'd really pay a bribe for that job?

42
00:02:56,140 --> 00:02:57,850
You'll be a famous author. Can't I have ambitions too?

43
00:02:59,310 --> 00:03:01,880
I have to at least become a lecturer to be a boyfriend you're proud of.

44
00:03:06,190 --> 00:03:08,720
- Then you should have told me.
- And how was I supposed to do that?

45
00:03:09,060 --> 00:03:10,190
You would've been ashamed.

46
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:12,190
You can only brag about a professor boyfriend.

47
00:03:12,890 --> 00:03:14,230
Because you're embarrassed I'm a driver,

48
00:03:14,660 --> 00:03:16,100
you lied to them too, didn't you?

49
00:03:19,230 --> 00:03:20,600
While I'm losing sleep...

50
00:03:20,870 --> 00:03:22,769
driving drunk jerks around,

51
00:03:22,770 --> 00:03:24,710
while you're having interviews and going to award shows.

52
00:03:24,970 --> 00:03:26,780
And what? Designer clothes?

53
00:03:28,080 --> 00:03:30,180
You think I'll be grateful for thousand-dollar clothes?

54
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:32,350
Why did you even ask me to come today?

55
00:03:32,780 --> 00:03:35,620
Did you need a pathetic accessory to wear that outfit and applaud you?

56
00:03:37,020 --> 00:03:39,520
- You jerk.
- You want me to be more honest?

57
00:03:40,060 --> 00:03:43,630
I have absolutely no desire to congratulate you on your award.

58
00:03:44,190 --> 00:03:46,400
When you got congratulatory calls, I felt like trash.

59
00:03:46,660 --> 00:03:50,400
I felt like a freeloading parasite, and it made me sick to my stomach!

60
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:00,240
So?

61
00:04:04,550 --> 00:04:05,550
So, what?

62
00:04:06,620 --> 00:04:09,320
You're trying to get me to break up, aren't you?

63
00:04:10,350 --> 00:04:12,690
You say it. Say you want to break up.

64
00:04:18,590 --> 00:04:19,660
Well?

65
00:04:20,230 --> 00:04:21,530
You can't even say the words?

66
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:25,400
Darn.

67
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:32,910
You pathetic fool.

68
00:05:18,590 --> 00:05:20,360
Get up. Let's go.

69
00:05:39,140 --> 00:05:40,210
You know something?

70
00:05:41,510 --> 00:05:43,380
Jun Kyung lies all the time.

71
00:05:45,350 --> 00:05:47,520
Deep down, she's really weak,

72
00:05:48,580 --> 00:05:51,220
but she pretends to be strong, pretends she's okay.

73
00:05:52,050 --> 00:05:53,620
She pretends to have it all together,

74
00:05:54,490 --> 00:05:56,320
always acting like nothing bothers her.

75
00:05:59,530 --> 00:06:01,330
And she's a terrible liar too.

76
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:08,100
Before,

77
00:06:09,070 --> 00:06:10,940
whenever something was wrong with Jun Kyung,

78
00:06:11,970 --> 00:06:15,680
she'd tell me every little detail.

79
00:06:17,350 --> 00:06:20,620
But since she met you, having her do that...

80
00:06:22,450 --> 00:06:23,520
gotten really rare.

81
00:06:26,050 --> 00:06:28,920
I'll admit I'm a little bummed about it.

82
00:06:29,590 --> 00:06:31,530
I kind of hold it against you, actually.

83
00:06:31,830 --> 00:06:32,830
But...

84
00:06:34,860 --> 00:06:36,500
I guess that's to be expected.

85
00:06:37,300 --> 00:06:38,370
That's why...

86
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:41,240
when I got her call today,

87
00:06:42,540 --> 00:06:43,610
I was like, "Yes!"

88
00:06:45,110 --> 00:06:46,680
I was so excited.

89
00:06:50,810 --> 00:06:53,110
But she won't tell me what's wrong.

90
00:06:55,350 --> 00:06:56,990
So I didn't push it.

91
00:06:57,850 --> 00:06:58,890
But...

92
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:03,590
The Jun Kyung I used to know wasn't like this.

93
00:07:05,630 --> 00:07:08,160
She'd get angry when she was angry,

94
00:07:09,760 --> 00:07:11,330
and she'd cry when she needed to.

95
00:07:13,370 --> 00:07:14,400
Do you...

96
00:07:15,300 --> 00:07:16,640
know what I mean?

97
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:21,440
I do.

98
00:07:24,210 --> 00:07:25,680
Don't make me laugh.

99
00:07:26,310 --> 00:07:27,650
You have no idea.

100
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:31,720
She just kept saying it was all her fault.

101
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:34,390
Okay, fine.

102
00:07:34,890 --> 00:07:37,830
I'm sure Jun Kyung did something wrong.

103
00:07:38,060 --> 00:07:40,160
But even so,

104
00:07:42,030 --> 00:07:43,870
I'm always on her side, no matter what.

105
00:07:45,670 --> 00:07:48,200
I'm completely biased.

106
00:07:50,470 --> 00:07:51,570
Thank you.

107
00:07:56,140 --> 00:07:57,250
From now on,

108
00:07:58,710 --> 00:08:01,220
please always be on her side.

109
00:08:22,700 --> 00:08:24,310
I'm holding you to that.

110
00:08:31,450 --> 00:08:33,780
- Where's Jun Kyung?
- She passed out.

111
00:08:34,380 --> 00:08:35,720
My gosh.

112
00:08:37,490 --> 00:08:39,520
Thanks for bringing Soo Jin home, Do Hyun.

113
00:08:40,690 --> 00:08:41,720
And for Jun Kyung too.

114
00:08:43,590 --> 00:08:44,590
Get home safe.

115
00:08:46,490 --> 00:08:47,530
Let's go.

116
00:09:31,210 --> 00:09:32,310
I'm sorry.

117
00:10:08,310 --> 00:10:10,910
Hey. What are you doing? Eat up.

118
00:10:12,550 --> 00:10:13,780
Your noodles are getting soggy.

119
00:10:14,750 --> 00:10:15,750
Right.

120
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:38,010
(Management Office)

121
00:10:51,190 --> 00:10:52,190
Ja Yeong.

122
00:10:57,490 --> 00:10:58,490
Ja Yeong.

123
00:11:12,810 --> 00:11:13,980
She...

124
00:11:14,610 --> 00:11:16,580
My wife has Alzheimer's disease.

125
00:11:16,980 --> 00:11:18,910
Her phone's off. The battery must be dead.

126
00:11:18,950 --> 00:11:21,050
I've searched everywhere around our campsite.

127
00:11:21,380 --> 00:11:23,820
We don't have any neighbours, so there's nowhere for her to go.

128
00:11:23,890 --> 00:11:26,960
We're reviewing the security video. Just give us a moment.

129
00:11:27,490 --> 00:11:31,060
- Okay.
- This is the only road out of camp.

130
00:11:32,830 --> 00:11:34,200
She could've gone toward the mountain.

131
00:11:36,730 --> 00:11:39,900
- Has this ever happened before?
- No, this is the first time.

132
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:43,910
- Is this you right here, sir?
- Yes, that's me.

133
00:11:46,370 --> 00:11:47,610
Could this be her?

134
00:11:48,680 --> 00:11:50,409
It looks like she's looking at you, sir.

135
00:11:50,410 --> 00:11:52,950
She seems to be looking at you while on the phone.

136
00:11:53,010 --> 00:11:54,720
(Palbon Village Intersection)

137
00:11:55,580 --> 00:11:56,890
You didn't run into her then?

138
00:12:09,260 --> 00:12:12,270
(Palbon Village Intersection)

139
00:12:14,940 --> 00:12:17,940
(Palbon Police Substation)

140
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:35,390
A work dinner?

141
00:12:36,560 --> 00:12:38,130
You didn't mention that.

142
00:12:38,890 --> 00:12:40,530
Yes, it was a last-minute thing.

143
00:12:41,260 --> 00:12:43,530
It's one I can't get out of.

144
00:12:44,030 --> 00:12:45,600
So I'm probably going to be pretty late.

145
00:12:46,270 --> 00:12:47,300
All right.

146
00:12:47,700 --> 00:12:51,810
It's been a while. Have some drinks and enjoy yourself.

147
00:12:51,970 --> 00:12:55,540
Okay, don't wait up. Go on to bed.

148
00:13:00,380 --> 00:13:02,380
(Bus Stop)

149
00:13:27,610 --> 00:13:28,710
Hey, Ja Yeong.

150
00:13:29,280 --> 00:13:30,350
Jin Ho.

151
00:13:30,910 --> 00:13:32,080
Did you get on the bus?

152
00:13:32,980 --> 00:13:34,680
No, not yet.

153
00:13:41,090 --> 00:13:42,120
Jin Ho.

154
00:13:44,030 --> 00:13:45,590
So where are you right now?

155
00:13:46,630 --> 00:13:49,000
Listen, Ja Yeong, they're calling for me.

156
00:13:49,460 --> 00:13:52,270
I'll take a cab home, so don't wait up for me.

157
00:13:52,830 --> 00:13:53,840
I've got to go.

158
00:15:04,740 --> 00:15:05,840
Jin Ho...

159
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:08,840
I'm sorry.

160
00:15:11,480 --> 00:15:13,550
I've made things hard on you again.

161
00:15:16,080 --> 00:15:18,590
I truly wanted you to be happy.

162
00:15:20,350 --> 00:15:22,790
I thought I could be happy by your side too.

163
00:15:25,960 --> 00:15:27,800
But I guess that's not going to happen.

164
00:15:31,430 --> 00:15:32,470
Jin Ho.

165
00:15:34,740 --> 00:15:35,770
Jin Ho.

166
00:15:38,410 --> 00:15:39,440
Jin Ho.

167
00:15:43,850 --> 00:15:46,510
I don't know how long I'll have my memories,

168
00:15:50,250 --> 00:15:51,450
but I hope my last memory...

169
00:15:53,960 --> 00:15:55,920
is of you.

170
00:17:17,610 --> 00:17:18,640
Are you okay?

171
00:17:22,180 --> 00:17:25,310
I'm the one who was wrong. Why are you asking if I'm okay?

172
00:17:34,420 --> 00:17:36,220
You didn't do anything wrong.

173
00:17:41,300 --> 00:17:42,300
I'm the one...

174
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:44,430
who's sorry.

175
00:18:21,240 --> 00:18:23,300
Thank you for not letting me go.

176
00:19:48,260 --> 00:19:49,990
- Sir.
- Yes?

177
00:19:50,020 --> 00:19:51,390
You should go home for now.

178
00:19:52,060 --> 00:19:54,160
We've been in touch with the taxi company,

179
00:19:54,230 --> 00:19:56,500
so we'll call you the moment we hear from the driver.

180
00:19:57,930 --> 00:19:59,370
No, it's okay. I'll wait.

181
00:20:00,230 --> 00:20:02,300
But you've been waiting for so long.

182
00:20:06,810 --> 00:20:09,780
(Serving the community with integrity and care)

183
00:20:13,150 --> 00:20:14,480
As you may already know,

184
00:20:14,520 --> 00:20:17,120
a nursing home is different from a convalescent hospital.

185
00:20:17,450 --> 00:20:20,420
We focus on providing daily care, not medical treatment.

186
00:20:20,790 --> 00:20:23,560
We make sure our residents can eat their meals comfortably...

187
00:20:23,620 --> 00:20:25,930
and live in a safe environment.

188
00:20:26,190 --> 00:20:28,130
We provide care for all aspects of their daily lives.

189
00:20:28,230 --> 00:20:29,900
It's the easiest way to understand what we do.

190
00:20:33,500 --> 00:20:36,400
We have art classes, singing lessons,

191
00:20:36,700 --> 00:20:39,810
as well as exercise and a variety of other programs.

192
00:20:40,610 --> 00:20:42,910
Our staff members and professional caregivers...

193
00:20:43,280 --> 00:20:46,750
treat them like their own family, so you don't need to worry.

194
00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:51,990
So, will it be your father or your mother joining us?

195
00:20:55,220 --> 00:20:56,220
It's me.

196
00:21:11,070 --> 00:21:13,010
- Daniel.
- I'm not your son?

197
00:21:18,850 --> 00:21:19,850
Am I really...

198
00:21:23,250 --> 00:21:24,590
not your son?

199
00:21:31,890 --> 00:21:33,490
Why did you lie to me?

200
00:21:35,060 --> 00:21:36,330
Daniel, look at me.

201
00:21:37,100 --> 00:21:38,430
I wasn't trying to lie to you...

202
00:21:44,710 --> 00:21:46,710
I can't trust anyone anymore.

203
00:21:49,710 --> 00:21:50,740
Mom...

204
00:21:52,480 --> 00:21:53,510
is taking me...

205
00:21:55,050 --> 00:21:56,180
back to Germany.

206
00:22:00,920 --> 00:22:02,420
It's all over now.

207
00:22:04,230 --> 00:22:05,330
Nothing matters anymore.

208
00:22:20,210 --> 00:22:21,540
You knew too, didn't you?

209
00:22:23,610 --> 00:22:24,610
That day...

210
00:22:27,150 --> 00:22:28,850
when I came to see you...

211
00:22:33,450 --> 00:22:34,820
You knew even then, didn't you?

212
00:22:38,890 --> 00:22:42,500
You know how much I like you.

213
00:22:43,660 --> 00:22:45,500
So why? Why didn't you tell me?

214
00:22:48,640 --> 00:22:49,800
I didn't have the courage.

215
00:22:53,140 --> 00:22:57,140
I was afraid you'd get hurt. I'm so sorry, Daniel.

216
00:23:01,920 --> 00:23:03,380
Because you accepted me...

217
00:23:06,550 --> 00:23:08,090
and let me live with you,

218
00:23:10,720 --> 00:23:11,890
I was so...

219
00:23:14,300 --> 00:23:15,300
I was...

220
00:23:17,060 --> 00:23:18,830
I was just so happy.

221
00:23:18,900 --> 00:23:22,240
I know. I was happy too, son.

222
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:26,010
I really was so happy.

223
00:23:36,220 --> 00:23:38,950
None of that matters to me.

224
00:23:39,550 --> 00:23:40,550
I'm...

225
00:23:42,720 --> 00:23:44,090
still your dad,

226
00:23:45,730 --> 00:23:46,760
and you're my son.

227
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:51,600
Got it?

228
00:24:07,850 --> 00:24:09,880
Yes, this is Officer Park Dong Su from the Palbon Substation.

229
00:24:11,920 --> 00:24:12,920
Yes.

230
00:24:15,860 --> 00:24:16,960
Yes, you said you've located him?

231
00:24:21,960 --> 00:24:22,960
Yes.

232
00:24:28,770 --> 00:24:29,770
Yes, I see.

233
00:24:35,280 --> 00:24:38,180
This stop is the Ian City Promotion Hall.

234
00:24:38,580 --> 00:24:41,650
Next stop, Power Square Mall.

235
00:24:42,080 --> 00:24:46,720
("A Still Relationship")

236
00:24:56,760 --> 00:25:00,170
(The hit new novel, "A Still Relationship" by Ji Hye On)

237
00:25:04,970 --> 00:25:11,010
("A Still Relationship")

238
00:25:11,610 --> 00:25:13,250
(Ji Hye On)

239
00:25:30,300 --> 00:25:33,500
(Professor Song Won Cheol)

240
00:25:38,140 --> 00:25:39,170
Tonight,

241
00:25:40,810 --> 00:25:43,780
with the guy who's always been there for me,

242
00:25:45,110 --> 00:25:47,210
instead of some fancy steak and whiskey,

243
00:25:48,880 --> 00:25:51,790
I want to celebrate with a beer and a pork cutlet from our local joint.

244
00:25:54,090 --> 00:25:55,390
And tomorrow night...

245
00:25:57,120 --> 00:25:58,560
and the night after that...

246
00:25:58,630 --> 00:26:00,760
(On the 29th night of summer, Ji Hye On)

247
00:26:00,830 --> 00:26:04,800
I want to tell him I just want us to stay like this forever.

248
00:26:06,630 --> 00:26:12,070
("A Still Relationship")

249
00:26:27,590 --> 00:26:28,790
Aren't you going to answer that?

250
00:26:30,890 --> 00:26:32,190
Your mom must be worried.

251
00:26:34,090 --> 00:26:35,100
I don't want to.

252
00:26:49,210 --> 00:26:50,240
Let's eat first.

253
00:26:51,550 --> 00:26:53,350
You must be starving. You haven't eaten anything.

254
00:26:54,780 --> 00:26:57,420
Eat up, and then I'll take you home.

255
00:27:15,140 --> 00:27:16,900
(Police)

256
00:27:19,340 --> 00:27:20,370
Are you Daniel?

257
00:27:24,810 --> 00:27:26,810
- Yes.
- Your mother reported you missing.

258
00:27:27,820 --> 00:27:30,880
She said you weren't taking calls and thought you were here.

259
00:27:32,120 --> 00:27:33,320
Come out, Daniel.

260
00:27:35,760 --> 00:27:36,790
What do you think you're doing?

261
00:27:37,390 --> 00:27:40,060
What's it to you? What are you, Daniel's dad?

262
00:27:41,800 --> 00:27:42,860
What do you think you're doing?

263
00:27:43,400 --> 00:27:45,670
Please bring my son out here.

264
00:27:48,440 --> 00:27:50,670
Is this woman your mother?

265
00:27:56,210 --> 00:27:58,510
And is he your father?

266
00:28:09,290 --> 00:28:11,960
For now, I think it's best if you go with your mom.

267
00:28:28,780 --> 00:28:30,780
- Daniel.
- Sir.

268
00:28:32,180 --> 00:28:33,350
This is the last time.

269
00:28:33,810 --> 00:28:36,080
You will never see Daniel again.

270
00:28:55,540 --> 00:28:56,540
Daniel.

271
00:29:04,210 --> 00:29:05,910
Don't cry. You're not a little kid anymore.

272
00:29:08,050 --> 00:29:09,250
What are you doing?

273
00:29:11,890 --> 00:29:13,390
No matter what anyone else says,

274
