332
00:35:25,260 --> 00:35:26,260
Loneliness.

333
00:35:29,730 --> 00:35:31,830
Which brings me to a question.

334
00:35:32,470 --> 00:35:36,200
Do you have a favourite line from the book?

335
00:35:36,640 --> 00:35:40,910
- Sorry?
- I'm sure you love all you wrote,

336
00:35:41,370 --> 00:35:45,880
but our Night Walk family is curious to know your absolute favourite.

337
00:35:57,290 --> 00:36:00,460
Noticing the shadow on Emma's face, Ryan asked,

338
00:36:01,930 --> 00:36:02,930
"What's wrong?"

339
00:36:06,470 --> 00:36:08,100
"The milk bottles in front of my neighbour's door..."

340
00:36:08,570 --> 00:36:12,170
"kept piling up, so I rang his bell."

341
00:36:13,740 --> 00:36:15,440
"But no one answered."

342
00:36:18,510 --> 00:36:19,510
"It was a lonely death."

343
00:36:22,950 --> 00:36:23,950
"A lonely death?"

344
00:36:25,450 --> 00:36:26,450
"Yes."

345
00:36:27,690 --> 00:36:28,990
"He died from loneliness."

346
00:36:31,960 --> 00:36:34,190
"Then, after a long silence, Emma spoke."

347
00:36:36,260 --> 00:36:37,430
"Isn't that terrifying?"

348
00:36:38,770 --> 00:36:39,770
"The thought that loneliness..."

349
00:36:40,900 --> 00:36:43,040
"can actually be a cause of death."

350
00:36:49,240 --> 00:36:50,940
"Ryan held Emma in his arms."

351
00:36:55,420 --> 00:36:56,650
"And he told her,"

352
00:36:59,890 --> 00:37:01,250
- "It's why some people..." - "It's why some people..."

353
00:37:04,690 --> 00:37:05,860
