436
00:46:40,030 --> 00:46:44,400
they're too embarrassed to reach out.

437
00:46:45,240 --> 00:46:48,270
I'm sorry. Did I overstep?

438
00:46:49,210 --> 00:46:50,210
No.

439
00:46:51,240 --> 00:46:52,410
I'm trying to thank you.

440
00:46:54,050 --> 00:46:55,510
For checking in on me and worrying.

441
00:46:58,580 --> 00:46:59,690
But...

442
00:47:00,850 --> 00:47:03,190
I have a concern of my own. May I ask you something?

443
00:47:04,190 --> 00:47:06,229
- Sure.
- Aren't you seeing anyone?

444
00:47:06,230 --> 00:47:07,230
Like a boyfriend?

445
00:47:09,160 --> 00:47:12,430
Spending a perfect day off like this with me, of all people.

446
00:47:15,870 --> 00:47:17,140
There was...

447
00:47:18,570 --> 00:47:19,870
someone I liked.

448
00:47:22,040 --> 00:47:24,780
"Was"? So you two broke up?

449
00:47:26,250 --> 00:47:27,250
No.

450
00:47:29,750 --> 00:47:31,780
He doesn't even know that I liked him.

451
00:47:33,050 --> 00:47:34,820
It was just a one-sided crush,

452
00:47:35,450 --> 00:47:37,420
and in the meantime, he got a girlfriend.

453
00:47:37,760 --> 00:47:40,790
What? If you started to like him,

454
00:47:41,390 --> 00:47:42,960
you should have told him.

455
00:47:45,770 --> 00:47:47,900
It's easy to like someone from afar,

456
00:47:49,500 --> 00:47:55,270
