I'll stop recognising all of you too.

540
00:53:55,200 --> 00:53:58,240
If I don't recognise you and hurt you,

541
00:53:58,840 --> 00:54:01,010
please don't hate me for it.

542
00:54:02,240 --> 00:54:07,080
I wanted to apologise in advance and ask you for this favour.

543
00:54:24,100 --> 00:54:25,730
Thank you, Jun Kyung,

544
00:54:26,700 --> 00:54:28,870
for throwing me such a lovely birthday party.

545
00:54:36,180 --> 00:54:40,210
Don't worry, Auntie. I think you'll be the last I forget.

546
00:54:40,610 --> 00:54:42,950
That charisma you had when we first met...

547
00:54:43,220 --> 00:54:44,950
How could I ever forget that?

548
00:54:48,620 --> 00:54:52,790
I'm going to make a wish and blow out my candles now.

549
00:56:03,800 --> 00:56:05,760
("A Still Relationship")

550
00:56:26,020 --> 00:56:27,120
You doing okay?

551
00:56:27,690 --> 00:56:30,220
What now? Did you call to pick a fight?

552
00:56:30,720 --> 00:56:32,790
No, I called to say congratulations.

553
00:56:34,290 --> 00:56:36,230
You're a real meteorologist now.

554
00:56:36,460 --> 00:56:39,000
But can I even trust your forecasts?

555
00:56:39,570 --> 00:56:40,570
Suit yourself.

556
00:56:41,030 --> 00:56:42,530
Now hurry up and pay me back.

557
00:56:42,830 --> 00:56:45,340
The second I get my paycheck, I'll pay you back first thing.

558
00:56:45,600 --> 00:56:46,740
Please do.

559
00:56:47,070 --> 00:56:48,240
I'm busy. I have to go.

560
00:56:52,080 --> 00:56:53,710
- Jun Kyung.
- What?

561
00:56:55,350 --> 00:56:56,550
It's supposed to rain tomorrow.

562
00:56:57,380 --> 00:56:58,420
Bring an umbrella.

563
00:56:59,990 --> 00:57:00,990
All right.

564
00:57:19,640 --> 00:57:21,810
Dad, are you doing okay?

565
00:57:22,570 --> 00:57:27,110
I'm great. The hospital treatment you suggested is going very well.

566
00:57:27,650 --> 00:57:30,280
These days, Ja Yeong is even better at finding her way around than I am.

567
00:57:32,550 --> 00:57:35,350
How have you been? Are the wedding plans coming along?

568
00:57:36,420 --> 00:57:37,420
Yes.

569
00:57:38,020 --> 00:57:40,990
Do Hyun and I went to an adoption agency yesterday.

570
00:57:41,290 --> 00:57:43,960
Really? That's great.

571
00:57:44,800 --> 00:57:49,230
Yes. But I'm still not sure about it.

572
00:57:51,470 --> 00:57:53,370
Take your time to think it over.

573
00:57:53,910 --> 00:57:56,680
Whatever you decide, I know you two will do great.

574
00:57:57,280 --> 00:57:58,280
Okay, Dad.

575
00:58:08,250 --> 00:58:09,690
Someone once said...

576
00:58:11,190 --> 00:58:12,760
that happiness is quiet...

577
00:58:14,090 --> 00:58:15,730
and misery is loud.

578
00:58:17,600 --> 00:58:19,530
In that sense, maybe happiness...

579
00:58:21,570 --> 00:58:23,540
is a lot like loneliness.

580
00:58:25,570 --> 00:58:26,840
Different in shape,

581
00:58:28,270 --> 00:58:29,540
different in colour,

582
00:58:31,180 --> 00:58:32,340
and different in size.

583
00:58:35,480 --> 00:58:37,350
The loneliness each of us feels.

584
00:58:41,390 --> 00:58:43,220
But if you trace it back to its source,

585
00:58:43,760 --> 00:58:46,760
they say you'll find love at the very end.

586
00:58:48,860 --> 00:58:51,860
When you crave something but can't have it,

587
00:58:53,330 --> 00:58:55,000
when you're left wanting,

588
00:58:57,870 --> 00:59:00,310
that feeling of emptiness is what becomes loneliness.

589
00:59:03,340 --> 00:59:07,650
When you look at it that way, maybe being lonely isn't so bad after all.

590
00:59:09,610 --> 00:59:11,820
It just hasn't been fulfilled yet,

591
00:59:13,250 --> 00:59:14,990
but at least it proves...

592
00:59:17,090 --> 00:59:18,560
that just as much love

593
00:59:21,130 --> 00:59:22,190
exists within my heart.

594
00:59:33,140 --> 00:59:35,640
(Love Me)

595
01:00:45,810 --> 01:00:50,280
(Thank you for watching Love Me.)
